reviewText: I love Cheech and Chong but I always hesitated buying these since they were around $15 a piece. I might of bought other Cheech and Chong movies for that amount but these were not as good as their first few efforts and I just couldn't just toss over $30 for both. I'm glad they did this because I could justify completing my collection of Cheech and Chong.The movies are funny but not Laugh out loud funny most of the time but they are Cheech and Chong and they have some fantastic moments. Don't expect a lot of features to these CD's you get some commentary and a bit of extras but not much.
summary: This is the only way I would buy them.
Title: Cheech & Chong's Nice Dreams & Things Are Tough All Over

reviewText: Well...if I am writing a review about a Cheech and Chong movie you KNOW that I obviously have all of the others(not yet, still missing 2 or 3 of them). Both good movies and got me all excited for the other ones in the series.
summary: Cheech and Chong's Double feature:Nice Dreams+Things Are Tough All Over
Title: Cheech & Chong's Nice Dreams & Things Are Tough All Over

reviewText: I SAW THIS MOVIES WHEN IT FIRST CAME OUT. IT WAS FUNNY BACK THEN, BUT I GUESS WITH AGE IT ISN'T QUITE AS FUNNY AS WHEN I WAS YOUNGER.
Title: Cheech & Chong's Nice Dreams & Things Are Tough All Over

reviewText: nice dreams looks to have been digitized by a trainee, the picture quality comes and goes with each scene. Some are clear, others are very reminiscent of the drive-in, which I personally enjoy, so after a few transitions I grew to enjoy the passing low video quality. "Tough all over" is perfect, so your hi-def tv will get along fine.No matter what the hardcore fans won't really care and you will enjoy! I did.Sage V.
Title: Cheech & Chong's Nice Dreams & Things Are Tough All Over

reviewText: I'm from this generation and while I was very straight, I can still appreciate this type of humor ;)  LOVE Cheech & Chong!  I like both these movies.  Things Are Tough All Over doesn't seem to have as many fans as Nice Dreams, but I'm in the minority in that I like TATAO much better.  Glad I found this double feature.
Title: Cheech & Chong's Nice Dreams & Things Are Tough All Over
